Class GraphOfTheGodsFactory

    Example Graph factory that creates a TitanGraph based on roman mythology. Used in the documentation examples and tutorials.

    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com)

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Calls TitanFactory.open(String), passing the Titan configuration file path which must be the sole element in the args array, then calls load(com.thinkaurelius.titan.core.TitanGraph) on the opened graph, then calls TitanGraph.close() and returns.

        This method may call System.exit(int) if it encounters an error, such as failure to parse its arguments. Only use this method when executing main from a command line. Use one of the other methods on this class (create(String) or load(com.thinkaurelius.titan.core.TitanGraph)) when calling from an enclosing application.

        Parameters:
        args - a singleton array containing a path to a Titan config properties file
